======================================
 JMeter CLI Parameter Cheat Sheet
======================================

Basic Test Execution:
---------------------
-n
    Run in non-GUI (command-line) mode. Required for automated runs.

-t <file.jmx>
    Path to the JMeter test plan file (.jmx).

-l <file.jtl>
    Path to save raw test results (JTL file). Used for generating reports later.

-j <file.log>
    Path to save the test log output (INFO, WARN, log.info() from Groovy etc.).


HTML Report Generation:
------------------------
-e
    Enables HTML report generation. Must be used with -o.

-o <folder>
    Output directory for the HTML report. 
    NOTE: Must not already exist, or JMeter will skip report generation.


User & System Properties:
--------------------------
-Jkey=value
    Sets a JMeter user-defined property.
    Accessible inside the test via ${__P(key)} or props.get("key").

-Dproperty=value
    Sets a Java system property.
    Can affect JMeter internals like working directory (-Duser.dir=...).


Example:
--------
jmeter -n -t API_Scaff.jmx ^
  -l results/results.jtl ^
  -j results/jmeter.log ^
  -e -o results/html ^
  -Jusers_file=../../../Shared/dev3_users.csv ^
  -Jthreads=5 -Jduration=60


Notes:
------
- Ctrl+C aborts the test, but skips HTML report generation.
- Always delete the report output folder before rerunning (-o must point to a clean directory).
- Use log tailing (e.g. `Get-Content -Wait` in PowerShell) to watch logs live.